description: Eniro AB engages in the operation of a search engine through the Internet, catalog, and mobile. The company is headquartered in Kista, Stockholm and currently employs 889 full-time employees. The company went IPO on 2000-10-10. Its offering allows users to find points of sale that have the products and services they are interested in. The Company’s information is made available through a number of distribution channels, Internet and mobile services, printed directories and other publications, as well as directory assistance services and Short Message Service (SMS) services. The company markets its products and services through such brands as eniro.se, Gula Sidorna, Din Del and Eniro 118 118 in Sweden; Gule Sider, Kvasir and Gule Sider 1880 in Norway; krak.dk, dgs.dk, Mostrup and Den Rode Lokalborg in Denmark; and Panorama Firm in Poland. The company operates through a number of subsidiaries in Denmark, Sweden, Norway, Finland and Poland.
naics: Newspaper, Periodical, Book, and Directory Publishers
